E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20redundancy%2C%20also%20known%20as%20being%20laid%20off%2C%20is%20a%20forced%20exit%20and%20a%20permanent%20loss%20of%20employment%20that%20occurs%20when%20employers%20need%20to%20reduce%20their%20workforce.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20been%20telling%20people%20bad%20news%20for%20nearly%2040%20years.%20It%20doesn't%20get%20any%20easier.%20I'm%20impacting%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20people%20in%20front%20of%20me%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20partners%20and%20family.%20It%20has%20a%20tremendous%20knock-on%20effect.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E30%20years%20ago%2C%20one%20of%20my%20previous%20bosses%20told%20me%20that%20I%20must%20never%20lose%20that%20sense%20of%20responsibility.%20Redundancies%20need%20to%20be%20handled%20very%20sensitively.%20It's%20important%20to%20me%20that%20the%20individual%20leaves%20the%20room%20with%20their%20head%20held%20high%2C%20knowing%20that%20they've%20been%20treated%20fairly%20and%20transparently.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20not%20unusual%20to%20be%20made%20redundant.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20employee%20has%20done%20nothing%20wrong.%20The%20average%20person%20will%20have%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fstories%2F2023%2F05%2Fworkers-multiple-careers-jobs-skills%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%2012%20jobs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20throughout%20their%20career%2C%20and%20redundancies%20can%20happen%20in%20that%20time.%20Between%20July%20and%20September%202024%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ons.gov.uk%2Femploymentandlabourmarket%2Fpeopleinwork%2Femploymentandemployeetypes%2Farticles%2Fimpactofreweightingonlabourforcesurveykeyindicators%2F2024https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ons.gov.uk%2Femploymentandlabourmarket%2Fpeopleinwork%2Femploymentandemployeetypes%2Farticles%2Fimpactofreweightingonlabourforcesurveykeyindicators%2F2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E90%2C000%20people%20were%20made%20redundant%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20future%20job%20interviews%2C%20hiring%20managers%20will%20usually%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20did%20you%20leave%20your%20last%20role%3F%26quot%3B%20Here's%20how%20to%20navigate%20having%20been%20laid%20off%20in%20an%20interview%20for%20a%20new%20job.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ffbb5f2-0f0d-4853-a9a8-388a4dd4740f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EBe%20transparent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDon't%20avoid%20the%20question.%20Be%20upfront%20and%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20left%20my%20previous%20company%20due%20to%20redundancy.%20There%20were%20a%20number%20of%20positions%20lost%2C%20and%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20I%20was%20one%20of%20those%20affected.%26quot%3B%20Provide%20a%20clear%20and%20concise%20explanation%20of%20the%20circumstances%2C%20and%20give%20specifics%20about%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20redundancy%20if%20you%20know%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDo%20not%20lie%20about%20layoffs.%20A%20skilled%20interviewer%20can%20see%20when%20people%20aren't%20being%20open.%20When%20you%20can%20see%20someone%20being%20dishonest%20as%20an%20interviewer%2C%20it%20gives%20negative%20signals%20about%20the%20candidate's%20character%20and%20resilience.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220bae01ab-7ae2-48c3-be1e-e545516f5c3d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EBe%20honest%20about%20your%20disappointment%2C%20but%20stress%20that%20you've%20moved%20on%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20fair%20to%20tell%20your%20interviewers%20that%20losing%20your%20job%20was%20a%20shock.%20You%20can%20say%20that%20it's%20a%20huge%20change%2C%20and%20that%20it's%20been%20disappointing%20or%20depressing.%20Expressing%20your%20feelings%20demonstrates%20emotional%20intelligence%2C%20showing%20that%20you%20can%20process%20challenges%20and%20learning%20from%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20open%20about%20the%20emotional%20impact%20of%20redundancy%20requires%20a%20balance.%20Ultimately%2C%20you%20should%20remain%20professional%20and%20focus%20on%20growth.%20Tell%20your%20interviewers%20that%2C%20after%20a%20period%20of%20reflection%2C%20you've%20moved%20forward.%20Interviewers%20typically%20respond%20positively%20to%20candidates%20who%20acknowledge%20their%20challenges%20while%20emphasizing%20how%20they've%20used%20the%20experience%20to%20grow%20and%20realign%20their%20career%20goals%2C%20not%20those%20who%20continue%20to%20be%20downhearted%20about%20their%20previous%20lives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234c23126-c18d-4fbc-a39c-4dedccf3492f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EFocus%20on%20the%20positives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20very%20possible%20to%20draw%20positives%20from%20your%20redundancy%20situation.%20It%20can%20be%20viewed%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20change%3A%20new%20skill%20opportunities%2C%20new%20ways%20of%20working%2C%20and%20new%20horizons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20you%20can%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20sad%20to%20leave%20my%20employer%20of%20X%20years.%20I've%20reflected%20on%20that%20and%20realized%20that%20it%20gave%20me%20the%20opportunity%20to%20be%20in%20a%20room%20with%20you%2C%20talking%20about%20my%20vision%20for%20the%20future%20and%20the%20skills%20and%20experiences%20that%20I%20can%20bring%20to%20this%20team.%20I'm%20very%20excited%20about%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20way%2C%20my%20redundancy%20has%20done%20me%20a%20favor%20because%20I'm%20enthused%2C%20energetic%2C%20and%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20future.%20Possibly%2C%20it's%20a%20change%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20undertaken%20had%20I%20not%20been%20forced%20to%2C%20but%20I'm%20embracing%20it%20as%20an%20opportunity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5a20c80-1696-4e5a-8f77-f3d45a3e992a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemain%20professional%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you're%20feeling%20resentment%20or%20anger%20about%20your%20redundancy%2C%20you%20need%20to%20handle%20this%20outside%20the%20interview.%20Candidates%20should%20see%20the%20interview%20room%20as%20a%20shop%20window%20to%20facilitate%20their%20potential%20entry%20into%20a%20new%20career.%20You%20have%20to%20go%20into%20that%20opportunity%20with%20your%20best%20efforts.%20It%20is%20not%20the%20time%20to%20express%20anger%20or%20recrimination.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDon't%20criticize%20your%20previous%20employer.%20You%20can%20use%20adverbs%20like%20%26quot%3Bsadly%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bdisappointingly%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bregrettably%26quot%3B%20when%20talking%20about%20your%20last%20job.%20The%20interviewer%20may%20pick%20up%20the%20subtle%20hints%20you%20weren't%20happy%20with%20how%20layoffs%20was%20handled.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dbd864a8-7690-489e-b2cc-5a4124af8ba5%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EHighlight%20your%20achievements%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20still%20important%20to%20discuss%20your%20achievements%20in%20your%20previous%20employment%2C%20even%20if%20you%20were%20made%20redundant.%20They%20don't%20go%20away.%20Share%20specific%20examples%20of%20how%20you%20met%20or%20exceeded%20expectations%20to%20reinforce%20your%20value%20and%20forward-thinking%20attitude.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJust%20because%20the%20business%20failed%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20failed.%20Be%20sure%20to%20share%20any%20details%20that%20give%20more%20context%20to%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20redundancy%20with%20interviewers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ca2a035a-b4ba-46a7-8d9e-07aa24663f27%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemember%20that%20redundancies%20are%20usually%20not%20the%20employee's%20fault%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20layoffs%20are%