beer%20and%20spirits%20comes%20as%20studies%20suggest%20drinking%20rates%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmu.edu%2Fdietrich%2Fnews%2Fnews-stories%2F2024%2Fmay%2Fcreswell-pandemic.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DResults%2520showed%2520that%2520these%2520young%2Csignificantly%2520fewer%2520alcohol%252Drelated%2520problems.%2C%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecreased%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20young%20Americans.%20Gallup%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F648413%2Falcohol-consumption-increasingly-viewed-unhealthy.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%20also%20indicates%20a%20shift%20in%20perception%20of%20alcohol.%20The%20report%20said%2045%25%20of%20Americans%20view%20alcohol%20as%20bad%20for%20health%2C%20which%20is%20a%206%25%20increase%20from%20the%20year%20before%20and%2017%25%20increase%20since%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsober-celebrities-who-dont-drink-do-drugs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDozens%20of%20celebrities%20have%20spoken%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20their%20sobriety%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20some%20even%20establishing%20their%20own%20non-alcoholic%20drink%20brands%2C%20including%20Katy%20Perry's%20De%20Soi%2C%20Blake%20Lively's%20Betty%20Buzz%2C%20and%20Tom%20Holland's%20Bero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShufelt%20said%20the%20availability%20of%20quality%20alternatives%20has%20given%20consumers%20the%20ability%20to%20drink%20non-alcoholic%20beer%20without%20changing%20their%20lifestyles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0d6170a-4b71-4131-b9d5-b9d17cc3cdd6%5C%22%3ELeaning%20into%20moderation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Athletic%20Brewing's%20CEO%20and%20Heineken%20USA's%20chief%20executive%2C%20Maggie%20Timoney%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20as%20more%20options%20are%20sold%20in%20bars%20and%20stores%2C%20buying%20behavior%20is%20leaning%20toward%20moderation%20over%20strict%20sobriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShufelt%20said%2080%25%20of%20Athletic%20Brewing%20customers%20still%20drink%20alcohol%2C%20suggesting%20that%20most%20of%20its%20customer%20base%20isn't%20traditionally%20sober.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeineken's%20Timoney%20pointed%20to%20NielsenIQ%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnielseniq.com%2Fglobal%2Fen%2Finsights%2Fanalysis%2F2024%2Fnon-alcohol-a-mindful-moderator-in-the-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202023%20that%20indicated%20over%2093%25%20of%20non-alcoholic%20consumers%20also%20purchased%20alcohol%2C%20a%2013%25%20jump%20from%20the%20year%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224873%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22three%20Heineken%200.0%20bottles%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677c45ac4fdf00939ed6758e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHeineken%200.0%20launched%20in%20the%20US%20in%202019.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Caparros%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Heineken%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shifting%20mindset%20toward%20drinking%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20trends%20like%20Dry%20January%2C%20which%20has%20evolved%20for%20some%20into%20the%20more%20flexible%20approach%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-prefer-damp-january-dry-january-drink-less-alcohol-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BDamp%20January%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20participants%20cut%20down%20on%20their%20alcohol%20intake%20for%20the%20month%20without%20fully%20eliminating%20it.%20Some%20have%20credited%20the%20less%20drastic%20approach%20for%20helping%20them%20moderate%20their%20alcohol%20consumption%20after%20the%20monthlong%20challenge%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETimoney%20said%20evolving%20attitudes%20toward%20non-alcoholic%20beverages%20stems%20in%20part%20from%20a%20desire%20to%20participate%20in%20occasions%20where%20others%20are%20drinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20linked%20to%20the%20health%20and%20wellness%20macro%20trend%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Heineken%20executive%20said%2C%20as%20well%20as%20occasions%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20people%20still%20want%20to%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20companies%20have%20been%20making%20non-alcoholic%20beer%20for%20more%20than%20half%20a%20decade.%20Athletic%20Brewing%20was%20launched%20in%202018.%20In%202019%2C%20Heineken%2C%20which%20has%20experimented%20with%20non-alcoholic%20beer%20in%20the%20past%2C%20launched%20the%20non-alcoholic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falcohol-brands-preparing-growing-nonalcoholic-market-heineken-constellation-anheuser-busch-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHeineken%200.0%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20other%20non-alcoholic%20drink%20companies%20like%20Free%20Spirits%20and%20Spiritless%20joined%20the%20space.%20Now%2C%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20non-alcoholic%20brands%20making%20the%20option%20to%20enjoy%20a%20mocktail%20or%20beer-like%20drink%20more%20widespread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthletic%20Brewing's%20Shufelt%20said%20that%20the%20proliferation%20of%20non-alcoholic%20options%20has%20expanded%20%26quot%3Bmenus%20and%20occasions%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20created%20excitement%20in%20the%20adult%20beverage%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilan%20Martin%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-spirits-ceo-surgeon-general-advisory-push-cultural-shift-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFree%20Spirits%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0told%20BI%20the%20rise%20of%20participants%20in%20Dry%20January%20and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbud-light-worst-year-beer-past-25-years-alcohol-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%20in%20some%20alcoholic%20drink%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0isn't%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20alcohol%20industry%20%26quot%3Bis%20in%20trouble%26quot%3B%20or%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20that%20people%20are%20now%20just%20drinking%20more%20mindfully%20and%20more%20with%20an%20eye%20to%20moderation%20because%20they%20have%20the%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224d9f03e5-3547-4284-8ae2-e3946aeb4a50%5C%22%3E'Bars%20and%20restaurants%20are%20leaving%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20on%20the%20table'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20sale%20of%20non-alcoholic%20beer%20and%20spirits%20has%20grown%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20segment%20is%20still%20a%20fraction%20of%20overall%20alcohol%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShufelt%20said%20the%20relative%20availability%20of%20non-alcoholic%20options%20is%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20the%20biggest%20friction%26quot%3B%20in%20people%20regularly%20buying%20the%20products.%20He%20said%20that%20Athletic%20Brewing%20products%20are%20on%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20restaurant%20menus%20in%20the%20US%20and%20as%20he%20sees%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bbars%20and%20restaurants%20are%20leaving%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20on%20the%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartin%20said%20that%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20drink%20moderately%2C%20it%20can%20be%20challenging%20%26quot%3Bif%20they%20have%20to%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20try%20your%20product%20or%20keep%20drinking%20your%20product.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20effort%20to%20reach%20more%20consumers%2C%20Heineken%20plans%20to%20expand%20its%200.0%20brand%20across%20two%20major%20US%20convenience%20retailer%20chains%20and%20launch%20a%2012-pack%20of%20the%20non-alcoholic%20beer%20bottles%20for%20the%20first%20time%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETimoney%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20stigmas%20around%20non-alcoholic%20beer%20are%20%26quot%3Beasing%2C%20they%20still%20remain%20a%20hurdle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Heineken%20study%20released%20on%20January%202%2C%20conducted%20in%20collaboration%20with%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford%2C%20surveyed%202%2C413%20Americans.%20The