20%26quot%3BStranger%26quot%3B%20Remark%20As%20Atul%20Subhash's%20Mother%20Seeks%20Grandson's%20Custody%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEnding%20weeks%20of%20suspense%20over%20the%20whereabouts%20of%20AI%20techie%20Atul%20Subhash's%20four-year-son%2C%20his%20estranged%20wife%20Nikita%20Singhania%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20that%20the%20child%20is%20at%20a%20boarding%20school%20in%20Haryana's%20Faridabad.%20Nikita's%20lawyer%20added%20that%20the%20child%20would%20be%20taken%20to%20Bengaluru%20where%20he%20can%20stay%20with%20his%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThirty-four-year-old%20Atul%20Subhash%20died%20by%20suicide%20in%20December%20after%20accusing%20Nikita%20and%20her%20family%20members%20of%20harassing%20him%20and%20his%20parents%20by%20filing%20false%20cases%20against%20them.%20Nikita%2C%20her%20mother%20Nisha%2C%20and%20her%20brother%20Anurag%20are%20facing%20an%20abetment%20to%20suicide%20case%20and%20are%20currently%20out%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAtul's%20mother%20Anju%20Devi%20has%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20seeking%20custody%20of%20her%20grandson.%20Nikita's%20lawyer%20told%20the%20court%20today%20that%20the%20four-year-old%20had%20been%20enrolled%20in%20a%20Faridabad%20boarding%20school%20and%20was%20there%20during%20her%20mother's%20arrest%20and%20subsequent%20bail.%20The%20child%20will%2C%20however%2C%20need%20to%20be%20shifted%20to%20Bengaluru%20because%20Nikita%20needs%20to%20be%20there%20as%20per%20the%20conditions%20of%20her%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20take%20the%20child%20to%20Bengaluru.%20We%20have%20taken%20the%20boy%20out%20of%20school.%20The%20mother%20has%20to%20remain%20in%20Bengaluru%20to%20fulfill%20bail%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20lawyer%20told%20the%20bench%20of%20Justice%20BV%20Nagarathna%20and%20Justice%20N%20Kotiswar%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20then%20directed%20that%20the%20child%20must%20be%20produced%20in%20court%20in%20the%20next%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyer%20representing%20Anju%20Devi%20told%20the%20court%20that%20as%20the%20grandmother%2C%20she%20should%20be%20given%20custody%20of%20the%20child.%20The%20lawyer%20said%20a%20child%20below%20six%20should%20not%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20boarding%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20child%20has%20barely%20spent%20time%20with%20his%20grandmother.%20%26quot%3BSorry%20to%20say%20but%20the%20child%20is%20a%20stranger%20to%20the%20petitioner%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Nagaratna%20remarked.%20Anju%20Devi's%20lawyer%20said%20they%20have%20pictures%20of%20the%20grandmother%20interacting%20with%20the%20child%20when%20he%20was%20two%20years%20old.%20Atul%20and%20Nikita%20married%20in%202019%20and%20had%20a%20son%20the%20next%20year.%20In%202021%2C%20Nikita%20left%20their%20Bengaluru%20home%20after%20an%20altercation%20and%20in%202022%2C%20she%20filed%20a%20case%20against%20Atul%20and%20his%20family%20members.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20stressed%20that%20Nikita%20Singhania%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20proven%20guilty%20and%20that%20it%20can't%20decide%20the%20matter%20based%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bmedia%20trial%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20child's%20custody%20will%20have%20to%20be%20taken%20up%20in%20the%20appropriate%20court%20where%20the%20trial%20is%20on.%20The%20next%20hearing%20on%20the%20matter%20is%20on%20January%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAtul%20Subhash%20died%20by%20suicide%20at%20his%20Bengaluru%20flat%20on%20December%209.%20In%20an%2081-minute%20video%20and%20a%2024-page%20suicide%20note%2C%20the%20techie%20accused%20Nikita%20and%20his%20family%20members%20of%20filing%20false%20cases%20against%20him%20and%20his%20parents%20to%20extort%20money%20from%20them.%20He%20also%20alleged%20that%20the%20justice%20system%20is%20biased%20to%20favour%20women%20in%20such%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20triggered%20outrage%20and%20a%20nationwide%20debate%20on%20the%20misuse%20of%20laws%20created%20to%20protect%20women%20from%20cruelty%20by%20husband%20or%20in-laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736240880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F28a2tum_atul-subhash-son_625x300_11_December_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fatul-subhash-suicide-case-nikita-singhania-bengaluru-techie-suicide-where-is-atul-subhashs-son-nikita-singhanias-lawyer-replies-in-top-court-7418358%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ending%20weeks%20of%20suspense%20over%20the%20whereabouts%20of%20AI%20techie%20Atul%20Subhash's%20four-year-son%2C%20his%20estranged%20wife%20Nikita%20Singhania%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20that%20the%20child%20is%20at%20a%20boarding%20school%20in%20Haryana's%20Faridabad%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fatul-subhash-suicide-case-nikita-singhania-bengaluru-techie-suicide-where-is-atul-subhashs-son-nikita-singhanias-lawyer-replies-in-top-court-7418358%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20new%20place%20to%20complain%20about%20your%20boss%3A%20LinkedIn%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Employee%20sitting%20at%20a%20desk%2C%20working%20on%20a%20laptop%20with%20a%20rain%20cloud%20hovering%20above%20them%2C%20LinkedIn%20logo%20glowing%20brightly%20on%20the%20laptop%20screen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6776f560e5726ab18d0e5668%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStefanie%20Costi%20knew%20the%20pressure%20was%20mounting%20for%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eboss%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20family-law%20attorney%20in%20Australia%2C%20Costi%20was%20used%20to%20tense%20situations.%20Trials%20were%20always%20stressful%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmass-torts-lawsuits-lawyers-settlements-strippers-hard-partying-money-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20firm%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20leading%20up%20to%20a%20major%20case's%20court%20date%2C%20last-minute%20tasks%20added%20to%20the%20strain.%20One%20day%20her%20boss%20was%20standing%20in%20his%20office%20trying%20to%20organize%20some%20files%20when%20he%20had%20an%20outburst.%20%26quot%3BHere%2C%20you%20fix%20it!%26quot%3B%20he%20shouted%2C%20she%20recalls.%20He%20threw%20the%20case%20file%20at%20her%20head%2C%20she%20jumped%20away%2C%20and%20it%20hit%20a%20bookshelf%2C%20bursting%20open%20and%20scattering%20papers%20and%20folders%20across%20the%20floor%2C%20she%20says.%20Costi%20stared%20at%20her%20manager%20in%20disbelief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECosti%20recalls%20that%20behavior%20like%20this%20was%20all%20too%20common%20at%20the%20firm.%20Managing%20partners%20like%20her%20boss%20routinely%20belittled%20employees.%20One%20even%20put%20up%20a%20sign%20in%20the%20hallway%20that%20said%20%26quot%3BNo%20whining%20about%20the%20long%20hours.%20If%20you%20can't%20cope%2C%20we'll%20replace%20you%20in%20a%20heartbeat.%26quot%3B%20Costi%20says%20multiple%20colleagues%20described%20having%20panic%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20reported%20her%20boss'%20behavior%20to%20HR%20but%20found%20those%20managers%20dismissive%20and%20ineffective.%20Eventually%20she%20decided%20she'd%20had%20enough%20and%20left%20the%20firm.%20Then%20some%20time%20after%20she%20landed%20at%20another%20firm%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20share%20her%20experiences%20on%20the%20platform%20where%20she%20may%20find%20a%20future%20employer%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20there%20was%20a%20bright%20young%20lawyer.%20She%20was%20bullied%20at%20work.%20It%20ruined%20her%20confidence%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20post%20began%2C%20before%20revealing%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20lawyer%20was%20me.%26quot%3B%20Costi's%20vulnerability%20stood%20out%20amid%20the%20job%20listings%2C%20team%20camaraderie%2C%20and%20humblebragging.%20It%20garnered%20more%20than%201.2%20million%20views%20and%20nearly%2010%2C000%20likes.%20Many%20of%20the%20more%20than%201%2C500%20people%20who%20commented%20on%20the%20post%20(and%20the%20thousand%20who%20messaged%20Costi%20directly)%20shared%20their%20own%20stories%20of%20toxic%20bosses%20and%20workplaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECosti%20was%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20response.%20%26quot%3BIt%20hit%20me%20hard%20how%20many%20others%20are%20suffering%20in%20silence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20began%20posting%20more%20stories%20about%20toxicity%20at%20her%20former%20firm%20and%20shared%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20handle%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-being-managed-out-according-to-anti-bullying-lawyer-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eworkplace%20bullying%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20harassment.%20She%20changed%20her%20LinkedIn%20title%20to%20The%20Anti-Bullying%20Lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%20the%2034-year-old%20has%20more%20than%2080%2C000%20followers.%20A%20few%20times%20a%20week%20she%20publishes%20a%20post%20%E2%80%94%20often%20several%20hundred%20words%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20selfie%20in%20which%20she's%20holding%20up%20a%20whiteboard%20with%20a%20handwritten%20summary%20of%20that%20post%2C%20like%20%26quot%3BA%20toxic%20boss%20will%20use%20a%20performance%20improvement%20plan%20to%20control%20you%2C%20not%20to%20help%20you.%26quot%3B%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-of-toxic-workplace-how-identify-spot-interview-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etoxic%20boss%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20writes%20in%20one%20post%2C%20will%20%26quot%3Bshower%20you%20with%20praise%20when%20you%20meet%20their%20expectations%20but%20withhold%20recognition%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bexploit%20your%20fear%20of%20failure%20to%20push%20you%20beyond%20reasonable%20limits.%26quot%3B%20Each%20post%20typically%20gets%20thousands%20of%20comments%20(most%20empathetic%2C%20some%20disparaging)%20from%20workers%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECosti%20is%20far%20from%20alone.%20Amid%20a%20fracturing%20social-media%20landscape%20and%20the%20decline%20of%20company%20loyalty%20and%20other%20evolving%20tensions%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-loyalty-gen-z-millennials-gen-x-boomers-employee-engagement-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployees%20and%20employers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20LinkedIn%20has%20grown%20looser%20and%20weirder%2C%20more%20personal%20and%20more%20combative.%20To%20some%2C%20the%20professional%20networking%20platform%20has%20become%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-is-a-dating-app-remote-work-online-romance-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edating%20site%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20others%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-hottest-comedy-club-linkedin-satire-unhinged-ceos-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecomedy%20club%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%20a%20new%20type%20of%20LinkedIn%20influencer%20has%20also%20emerged%2C%20one%20who%20instead%20of%20touting%20how%20to%20maximize%20your%20productivity%20and%20get%20the%20best%20out%20of%20your%20workplace%20shines%20a%20light%20on%20the%20darkest%20corners%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20growing%20cadre%20of%20influencers%20and%20their%20followers%20share%20advice%20on%20identifying%2C%20navigating%2C%20and%20escaping%20toxic%20workplaces.%20Posts%20from%20professionals%20telling%20stories%20about%20their%20%26quot%3Bawful%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bhorrible%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bterrible%26quot%3B%20bosses%20abound.%20They%20tend%20to%20see%20human%20resources%20as%20an%20extension%20of%20corporate%20dogma%20meant%20to%20reinforce%20company%20policies.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20human%20or%20resourceful%20about%20HR%20in%20a%20toxic%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20Costi%20writes%20in%20one%20post.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20HR%20Isn't%20Your%20Friend%20in%20Uncovering%20Toxic%20Work%20Cultures%2C%26quot%3B%20begins%20a%20post%20from%20a%20Canadian%20career%20coach%20with%20nearly%20200%2C000%20followers.%20Instead%2C%20they%20see%20a%20better%20path%20to%20healthier%20workplaces%20in%20forming%20a%20community%20of%20empathizers%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20where%20workers%20can%20share%20their%20stories%20and%20commiserate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20HR%20professionals%20I%20talked%20to%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20were%20alarmed%20by%20the%20uptick%20they'd%20seen%20in%20posts%20about%20bad%20bosses%20and%20noxious%20office%20behavior.%20They%20caution%20that%20if%20workers%20bypass%20HR%20and%20take%20complaints%20to%20LinkedIn%2C%20they%20risk%20doing%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20toxicity%20%E2%80%94%20a%20broad%20term%20encompassing%20infighting%2C%20intimidation%2C%20belittling%2C%20and%20other%20affronts%20%E2%80%94%20harms%20the%20productivity%20and%20mental%20health%20of%20employees%20across%20the%20workforce.%20In%20a%202023%20survey%20from%20the%20American%20Psychological%20Association%2C%2022%25%20of%20workers%20said%20they%20had%20experienced%20mental%20harm%20at%20work%2C%20and%20the%20same%20percentage%20of%20workers%20said%20they%20had%20experienced%20harassment.%20The%20APA%20said%20that%20in%20the%202024%20version%20of%20the%20survey%2C%2059%25%20of%20respondents%20indicated%20their%20employer%20%26quot%3Bthinks%20their%20work%20environment%20is%20a%20lot%20mentally%20healthier%20than%20it%20actually%20is.%26quot%3B%20A%202024%20report%20by%20the%20human-resources%20software%20provider%20HR%20Brain%20said%20that%2037%25%20of%20workers%20suggested%20they%20experienced%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-ceos-than-workers-think-their-company-culture-is-toxic-2024-6%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520findings%2520on%2520toxicity%2520at%2Creport%2520suffering%2520mental%252Dhealth%2520issues.%26amp%3Btext%3DBut%2520hold%2520up.%2Cposition%2520to%2520solve%2520the%2520problem.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20toxic%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20daily%20and%20that%2032%25%20identified%20their%20boss%20as%20a%20primary%20source%20of%20stress%20and%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToxic%20behavior%20in%20the%20workplace%20is%20an%20ever%20present%20issue%20with%20the%20power%20to%20significantly%20undermine%20company%20culture%2C%20team%20morale%2C%20and%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Joe%20Galvin%2C%20the%20chief%20research%20officer%20of%20the%20executive%20coaching%20firm%20Vistage.%20%26quot%3BThe%20rise%20of%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20work%20has%20blurred%20traditional%20boundaries%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20toxic%20behaviors%20to%20slip%20by%20unnoticed.%26quot%3B%20Email%20and%20messaging%20is%20more%20common%20with%20remote%20workers%20who%20otherwise%20might%20just%20talk%20out%20a%20problem%20in%20person%20at%20the%20office%2C%20Galvin%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToxic%20behavior%20in%20the%20workplace%20comes%20in%20all%20shapes%20and%20sizes.%20Costi%20connected%20me%20to%20several%20colleagues%2C%20clients%2C%20and%20followers%20who%20had%20experienced%20a%20toxic%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeverly%20(who%20asked%20me%20to%20use%20a%20pseudonym%20for%20fear%20of%20retribution)%20was%20an%20up-and-coming%20lawyer%20at%20another%20firm%20in%20Australia.%20One%20day%20she%20approached%20a%20senior%20partner%20for%20advice%20on%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20excel%20and%20be%20promoted%20at%20the%20firm.%20%26quot%3BShe%20invited%20me%20into%20her%20office%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20close%20the%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20Beverly%20recounts%20over%20email.%20%26quot%3BShe%20tried%20to%20convince%20me%20that%20I%20couldn't%20succeed%20in%20her%20practice%20area%26quot%3B%20and%20pressured%20Beverly%20to%20watch%20graphic%20footage%20from%20one%20of%20her%20cases%2C%20%26quot%3Bincluding%20a%20prison%20gang%20rape%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20scare%20me%20off.%26quot%3B%20Afterward%2C%20Beverly%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bshe%20warned%20me%20that%20she%20would%20sue%20me%20for%20defamation%20if%20I%20told%20anyone%20about%20her%20actions%20and%20threatened%20to%20make%20my%20life%20difficult%20at%20the%20firm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stefanie%20Costi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67781ea959d276c1cdaff64d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20few%20times%20a%20week%20Stefanie%20Costi%2C%20who%20goes%20by%20%26quot%3BThe%20Anti-Bullying%20Lawyer%26quot%3B%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20will%20make%20a%20lengthy%20post%20about%20navigating%20workplace%20toxicity%2C%20along%20with%20a%20selfie%20in%20which%20she%20holds%20a%20whiteboard%20sign%20summarizing%20the%20post.%3Cp%3EStefanie%20Costi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%20Beverly%20decided%20to%20leave%20the%20firm%2C%20but%20she%20remained%20concerned%20about%20the%20senior%20colleague.%20Beverly%20says%20she%20thought%20that%20if%20she%20stayed%20at%20the%20firm%20the%20colleague%20%26quot%3Bwould%20have%20harassed%20me%20outside%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20she%20has%20started%20to%20share%20her%20story%20more%20and%20will%20often%20comment%20on%20Costi's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%20posts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHelen%20Pamely%2C%20an%20attorney%20in%20Spain%2C%20also%20turned%20to%20LinkedIn%20as%20a%20place%20to%20talk%20about%20toxic%20work%20culture%20and%20help%20others%20dealing%20with%20bad%20behavior%20at%20work.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20quit%20companies.%20They%20quit%20bosses%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%20on%20LinkedIn%20recently.%20She%20now%20has%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20followers%20and%20posts%20often%20about%20the%20lessons%20she%20learned%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawyer-quit-career-live-in-her-car-travel-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20career%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20says%20the%20community%20the%20legal-industry%20LinkedIn%20posters%20are%20building%20represents%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%20turning%20point%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20a%20unique%20position%20%E2%80%94%20no%20longer%20tied%20to%20a%20firm%20%E2%80%94%20so%20I%20can%20speak%20pretty%20openly%20about%20cultural%20and%20systemic%20issues%20others%20can't%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20messages%20I%20receive%20thanking%20me%20for%20being%20that%20voice%20is%20overwhelming.%20The%20messages%20come%20from%20people%20of%20all%20levels%20of%20seniority.%26quot%3B%20She%20adds%20that%20%26quot%3Breal%2C%20positive%20change%20can%20only%20happen%20through%20honest%20and%20open%20conversations%20and%20helping%20people%20realize%20they%20aren't%20alone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ECosti%20says%20people%20are%20turning%20to%20LinkedIn%20because%20they%20aren't%20seeing%20results%20from%20channels%20like%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-problems-hr-cant-help-with-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20human%20resources%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHR%20is%20often%20more%20about%20protecting%20the%20company's%20interests%20than%20supporting%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20Costi%20says.%20%26quot%3BReporting%20toxic%20behavior%20can%20backfire%2C%20labeling%20you%20as%20a%20'troublemaker'%20and%20potentially%20putting%20your%20job%20at%20risk.%20The%20sad%20reality%20is%20that%20many%20toxic%20bosses%20are%20untouchable%2C%20insulated%20by%20the%20very%20system%20that's%20supposed%20to%20hold%20them%20accountable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Costi%2C%20as%20she%20often%20advises%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20what%20works%20is%20thoroughly%20documenting%20behavior.%20%26quot%3BKeep%20meticulous%20records%20of%20every%20incident%2C%20every%20conversation%2C%20every%20email%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20isn't%20just%20about%20protecting%20yourself.%20It's%20about%20building%20an%20undeniable%20case%20that%20even%20the%20company%20can't%20ignore.%20If%20HR%20won't%20take%20action%2C%20you%20can%20use%20this%20evidence%20to%20escalate%20the%20issue%2C%20either%20through%20legal%20channels%20or%20by%20finding%20a%20new%20role%20where%20you%20won't%20have%20to%20constantly%20look%20over%20your%20shoulder.%26quot%3B%20Costi%20says%20LinkedIn%20is%20a%20good%20place%20to%20find%20a%20community%20%E2%80%94%20though%20she%20does%20caution%20to%20avoid%20specifics%20like%20names%20or%20your%20place%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20agrees%20that%20LinkedIn%20is%20the%20right%20venue%20to%20tackle%20toxic%20workplaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPublicly%20airing%20grievances%20can%20erode%20respect%20within%20a%20team%20and%20contribute%20to%20a%20negative%20work%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Galvin%20says.%20%26quot%3BLeaders%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20fostering%20a%20culture%20of%20open%2C%20constructive%20communication%20and%20guiding%20employees%20to%20address%20concerns%20through%20appropriate%20internal%20channels.%20Regular%20check-ins%2C%20mentorship%20programs%2C%20and%20conflict-resolution%20strategies%20can%20help%20prevent%20issues%20from%20escalating%20to%20public%20social%20media.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Glowa%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20HR%20Brain%2C%20says%20that%20%26quot%3Brather%20than%20venting%20online%2C%20reporting%20helps%20build%20a%20proper%20case%20while%20ensuring%20confidentiality%20and%20protecting%20your%20professional%20reputation%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you%20post%20online%20can%20follow%20you%20indefinitely.%26quot%3B%20LinkedIn%20representatives%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20record%20about%20toxic%20culture%20and%20posting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%20argue%20that%20HR%20can%20be%20valuable%2C%20and%20there%20are%20certainly%20cases%20where%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20look%20into%20legal%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20Brenecki%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-prepare-what-say-layoff-termination-meeting-employment-lawyer-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20attorney%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%2C%20says%20that%20airing%20your%20dirty%20laundry%20about%20work%20on%20LinkedIn%20might%20be%20OK%20if%20you%20keep%20it%20vague.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20I%20would%20advise%20against%20publishing%20any%20factual%20statements%20regarding%20a%20specific%20company%20in%20the%20event%20there%20is%20litigation%20in%20the%20future%20stemming%20from%20the%20employee's%20allegations%20of%20a%20toxic%20workplace%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrenecki%20also%20notes%20why%20it%20might%20make%20sense%20to%20go%20to%20HR.%20If%20you're%20experiencing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjustin-baldoni-blake-lively-nyt-lawsuit-takeaways-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharassment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20discrimination%2C%20or%20other%20bad%20behavior%20at%20work%2C%20the%20company%20likely%20prefers%20that%20you%20go%20to%20HR%20so%20it%20can%20handle%20the%20situation%20according%20to%20state%20employment%20laws.%20If%20you%20don't%20go%20to%20HR%2C%20the%20company%20could%20later%20be%20found%20legally%20liable%20for%20allowing%20discrimination%20or%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20such%20a%20company%20does%20not%20maintain%20a%20properly%20functioning%20HR%20department%2C%20any%20violations%20of%20employment%20law%2C%20particularly%20intentional%20ones%2C%20will%20be%20their%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20experts%20say%20workplace%20toxicity%20ultimately%20won't%20be%20resolved%20by%20HR%2C%20the%20courts%2C%20or%20LinkedIn.%20They%20made%20the%20case%20for%20employees%20working%20out%20issues%20together%20and%20holding%20each%20other%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTechnology%20has%20given%20us%20more%20convenient%20escapes%20from%20the%20vulnerability%20required%20to%20solve%20relationship%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Joseph%20Grenny%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20the%20corporate%20training%20company%20VitalSmarts%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BCrucial%20Conversations.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BOur%20interpersonal%20muscles%20are%20atrophying%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20some%20of%20the%20loneliness%2C%20alienation%2C%20and%20disconnection%20that%20characterizes%20today's%20world.%26quot%3B%20He%20suggests%20that%20the%20answer%20might%20be%20found%20through%20tough%2C%20direct%20conversations%20with%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20important%20predictor%20of%20your%20capacity%20to%20be%20heard%20is%20how%20psychologically%20safe%20the%20other%20person%20feels%2C%26quot%3B%20Granny%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20believe%20your%20agenda%20is%20to%20hurt%20them%2C%20they%20will%20use%20their%20power%20against%20you.%20If%20they%20believe%20you%20care%20about%20their%20interests%20and%20concerns%20(as%20well%20as%20your%20own)%2C%20they%20are%20far%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20defensive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECosti%20argues%20that%20workplace%20toxicity%20is%20just%20too%20prevalent%20and%20that%20people%20don't%20feel%20safe%20going%20to%20HR%20or%20dealing%20with%20the%20issue%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20July%2C%20she%20founded%20a%20startup%20called%20The%20Rising%20Heard%2C%20which%20provides%20legal%20advice%2C%20coaching%2C%20and%20education%20to%20people%20who%20have%20experienced%20toxic%20workplaces.%20She%20plans%20to%20continue%20posting%20her%20whiteboard%20comments%20for%20all%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20faced%20trolling%20from%20those%20who%20deny%20the%20existence%20of%20such%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20I've%20considered%20these%20warnings%2C%20I%20always%20respond%20with%3A%20Standing%20up%20for%20what's%20right%20might%20be%20risky%2C%20but%20staying%20silent%20in%20the%20face%20of%20injustice%20is%20a%20far%20greater%20loss.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJohn%20Brandon%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20published%20over%2015%2C000%20articles%20on%20social%20media%2C%20technology%2C%20leadership%2C%20mentoring%2C%20and%20many%20other%20topics.%20He%20has%20published%20two%20books%20including%20his%20latest%2C%20The%20Seven%20Minute%20Productivity%20Solution.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-worker-uprising-hr-out-toxicity-bullying-linkedin-in-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736240761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6776f5819de00e389eb429bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-worker-uprising-hr-out-toxicity-bullying-linkedin-in-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fed%20up%20with%20company%20processes%20and%20human%20resources%2C%20people%20are%20reporting%20their%20horrible%20bosses%20on%20social%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(John%20Brandon)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-worker-uprising-hr-out-toxicity-bullying-linkedin-in-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%2